2. Model-View-Adapter (MVA)
3. Model-View-Presenter (MVP)
4. Model-View-ViewModel (MVVM) 

**MVC Architecture Explanation with Diagram:**

The Model-View-Controller (MVC) architecture is a design pattern that divides an application into three interconnected components:

1.  **Model**: Represents the data and business logic of the application.
2.  **View**: Handles user interactions and displays the output to the user.
3.  **Controller**: Acts as an intermediary between the Model and View, receiving input from the View, updating the Model, and updating the View accordingly.

**Diagram:**

```
                      +---------------+
                      |        View     |
                      +---------------+
                             |
                             |
                             v
                      +---------------+
                      |  Controller   |
                      |  (intermediary) |
                      +---------------+
                             |
                             |
                             v
                      +---------------+
                      |       Model    |
                      |  (data & logic)|
```
